City Power's Yumna Sheik says areas including Northcliff, Roosevelt Park and Victory Park have been affected. JOHANNESBURG Johannesburg City Power says its technicians are working hard to ensure that electricity is restored to all areas which have been without supply for parts of this weekend.The utility says several power outages were caused by the heavy rains across the province where some suburbs have been without electricity since Friday. City Power's Yumna Sheik says areas including Northcliff, Roosevelt Park and Victory Park have been affected.The outages have prompted some residents to protest outside the Roosevelt substation today.Sheik says demonstrators should not tamper with the sub-station. We are asking that residents don t get to the station and hinder work that is being done there. We apologise for this and our teams are doing the best they can. 